OL,3,C'He stole my childhood': Survivors on
OL,4,Crelease of paedophile from jail
OL,6,FSurvivor, Michelle Erwin felt the
OL,7,Fterror of Adams' crimes when she was a
OL,8,Fyoung girl.
OL,10,FShe said: "There is no saying sorry
OL,11,Ffor something like that. It's not like
OL,12,Fgoing into the shop and stealing a bar
OL,13,Fof chocolate. He stole my childhood."
OL,15,FThe news that the man who sexually
OL,16,Fabused her is set to be released from
OL,17,Fjail makes her "feel helpless".J"He's
OL,18,Fwon the battle, more or less, I feel
OL,19,Fdefeated, I feel numb.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776348651
OL,3,C'He stole my childhood': Survivors on
OL,4,Crelease of paedophile from jail
OL,6,F"He's a very, very manipulative man,
OL,7,Fso arrogant that he'd be coming out of
OL,8,Fjail and he'll have that sort of
OL,9,Fattitude of 'I've served my time',"
OL,10,Fshe added.
OL,12,F"As he's coming out, his goal is just
OL,13,Fgoing to be to reoffend. I have no
OL,14,Fdoubt about it. I am convinced of that
OL,15,Fthat is the first thing that he is
OL,16,Fgoing to do when he gets out."
OL,18,FJade Critchlow is also a survivor from
OL,19,FLiverpool and was 12-years-old when
OL,20,FAdams' entered her life.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776348651
OL,3,C'He stole my childhood': Survivors on
OL,4,Crelease of paedophile from jail
OL,6,FShe described him as "evil" and said
OL,7,Fhe should be kept in prison "because
OL,8,Fhe's just not going to change".
OL,10,FAdams is coming to the end of a life
OL,11,Fsentence at HMP Whatton in Nottingham
OL,12,Ffor horrific crimes against a
OL,13,Fschoolgirl in Northern Ireland.
OL,15,FHe had been eligible for release since
OL,16,F2013 but failed seven times to be
OL,17,Freleased because he was still viewed
OL,18,Fas too dangerous.
OL,20,FThe parole board in England confirmed
OL,21,Fto UTV, they authorised Adams' release.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/6
